{"word":"γνάθος","slug":"γνάθος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>γνάθος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>akin to <a href='S:γένυς'><el>γένυς</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>the jaw</i>, properly <i>the lower jaw</i>, <el>ἡ κάτω γν.</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>; <el>ἔπαγε γνάθον</el> take your <i>teeth</i> to it! <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; <a href='S:often'>oft.</a> in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> of fire, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> also, like <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>fauces</el>, of a <i>narrow strait</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>4. </b><i>the point</i> or <i>edge</i>, as of a wedge, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}